title: Minot Police investigating late-night gunshots on city's northeast side
content: MINOT, N.D. - Minot Police spent Friday night investigating reports of gunshots on the city’s northeast side.    Police say they responded to the area of the 200 block of 7th Avenue NE at 10:40 p.m., following reports of several gunshots in the area.    Investigators found three spent shell casings in the area but were unable to gather suspect information from witnesses.    Police conducted welfare checks on anyone in the area as well.    No one was hurt and police found no property damage.    The incident remains under investigation.
